content: You cannot submit the H1B form to me as I am a computer program and cannot receive or process physical or digital forms. The H1B visa application is a legal document and must be submitted to the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) through the proper channels. The USCIS website ([www.uscis.gov](http://www.uscis.gov)) provides information on the H1B visa application process, including the forms and documents that are required and the steps for submitting them. The forms and supporting documentation can be submitted electronically using the USCIS website or by mail. To submit the form electronically, you will need to create an account on the USCIS website and then use the online form to complete and submit the application.
